"x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:daily-idea-research"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Daily automated SaaS/web service idea research workflow for OpenClaw Bot. Use when: (1) The bot needs to run the daily idea generation and delivery workflow, (2) Automated discovery of SaaS opportunities with email delivery and Telegram notification, (3) Running the complete pipeline from trend discovery to user notification."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:deep-research"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"COMPREHENSIVE research for academic rigor and publication quality. Use when you need: (1) 40-85+ authoritative sources with quality ratings, (2) Academic, thesis, or publication-quality research, (3) Investment due diligence or critical fact-checking requiring source verification, (4) Transparent methodology with auditable research phases, (5) Literature reviews or comprehensive market analysis. Takes ~6-8 minutes. NOT for quick answers - use the 'research' skill instead for 2-minute overviews with 10-20 sources."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:docx"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Comprehensive document creation, editing, and analysis with support for tracked changes, comments, formatting preservation, and text extraction. When Claude needs to work with professional documents (.docx files) for: (1) Creating new documents, (2) Modifying or editing content, (3) Working with tracked changes, (4) Adding comments, or any other document tasks"]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:docx-draft"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Convert Word documents to structured markdown for LLM-assisted editing, then convert back to Word with preserved formatting. Use when you need to draft, edit, or work on .docx files interactively."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:docx-to-markdown"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Convert Microsoft Word documents (.docx) to clean, lightweight markdown optimized for LLM analysis and processing. Use when - (1) User asks to \"convert this docx to markdown\", \"export Word as markdown\", or \"turn .docx into .md\", (2) Analyzing, summarizing, or processing Word document content with an LLM, (3) Extracting text content from .docx files for AI processing without formatting bloat, (4) Creating a clean, readable markdown version of a Word document, (5) Preparing Word documents for LLM ingestion where formatting metadata is unnecessary. ALWAYS use this skill as the FIRST step when any LLM needs to analyze a Word document. Converts headers, bullet points, paragraphs, bold text, and basic tables to markdown. Related - docx conversion, Word to markdown, document analysis, extract text from Word, .docx to .md, convert document, Word file processing, Microsoft Word export, lightweight markdown, AI-friendly format, document parsing."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:docx-translator"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Translate documents (DOCX/PDF) between any language pair while preserving formatting, tables, and layout. Handles long documents via intelligent chunking. Use when: user needs to translate Word/PDF documents, formatting preservation is critical, documents contain tables/images/headers, or user mentions translation between languages."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:form-filler-chrome-daemon"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Fill complex multi-page forms in an already-open local Google Chrome session using DevTools remote debugging and daemon-backed CDP control. Use when the browser is already open, Chrome remote debugging is available, and you want direct live-tab automation without Playwright or VNC screenshots. Best for quote forms, applications, and registrations where the agent should reuse one approved tab, inspect the DOM directly, fill non-sensitive fields from a profile, and pause for sensitive details."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:form-filler-vnc-playwright"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Fill complex multi-page forms in VNC/X11 or agent-owned Chromium sessions using Playwright-based browser helpers and screenshot-driven interaction. Use when working inside shared VNC desktops, inherited browser windows, or Linux/X11 environments where the agent may need either a persistent Playwright helper or low-level X11/VNC clicks. Best for long-form workflows with human-in-the-loop pauses for sensitive details."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:frontend-blog"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Implement a complete headless blog with Decap CMS in any frontend project. Supports post scheduling via GitHub Actions, Netlify, or Vercel cron jobs. Works with React, Next.js, Astro, Vue, and other frameworks. Creates blog listing and post pages, handles images, and generates README_blog.md for agent documentation. Use when adding a blog to a SaaS frontend with scheduled publishing needs."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:frontend-design"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Create distinctive, production-grade frontend interfaces with high design quality. Use this skill when the user asks to build web components, pages, artifacts, posters, or applications (examples include websites, landing pages, dashboards, React components, HTML/CSS layouts, or when styling/beautifying any web UI). Generates creative, polished code and UI design that avoids generic AI aesthetics."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:github-fetch-issue"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"List and fetch issues from your own GitHub repositories only. Use when you need to view issues, get details of specific issues, filter by state/labels/assignees, or queue issues for execution. Verifies repository ownership before allowing access for security."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:github-log-issue"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Create GitHub issues on any repository (your own or others'). Use when you need to log bugs, feature requests, or tasks to GitHub Issues. Supports easy auto-detection for your own repos with --my-repo flag. Includes best practices guidance for writing effective issues."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:github-pr-original-repo"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Create pull requests from a forked repository to the original repository using GitHub API. Use when you have a fork with commits that should be contributed back to the original project. Automatically detects the original repository from fork metadata and creates PRs with proper branch references. Supports draft PRs, custom base/head branches, and dry-run mode for testing."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:github-push"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Push git commits to GitHub with intelligent protocol selection (SSH > gh CLI > HTTPS), auto-recovery from divergent branches, and repository creation. Use when pushing commits, creating repositories, handling authentication failures, or recovering from git sync conflicts. Handles both public and private repositories with automatic git configuration."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:github-repo-info"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Retrieve comprehensive GitHub repository details including README, language breakdown, contributors, stars, forks, and metadata. Use when: user asks about a specific repo (e.g., 'facebook/react'), investigating a library/tool, checking repo activity/maintenance, reading README docs, or analyzing tech stack. ALWAYS use AFTER github-search-repos or github-trending for full details on found repositories."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:github-search-repos"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Search public GitHub repositories by keywords, topics, language, stars, and other criteria. Use to discover repos matching specific themes or technologies."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:github-trending"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Discover trending and recently popular GitHub repositories. Find new projects gaining traction, by language, topic, or overall."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:gmail-search"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Search and fetch emails from Gmail using IMAP with App Password authentication. Use when: searching emails by subject/sender/date/body, listing emails from specific senders, fetching full email content with attachments, filtering by size or attachment status, or accessing Gmail for email analysis. Requires Gmail with 2FA and App Passwords."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:gmail-send"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Send emails via Gmail using SMTP with App Password authentication. Use when: sending email reports/notifications, automated alerts/summaries, emailing files/attachments, or sending HTML/plain text emails programmatically. Requires Gmail with 2FA and App Passwords."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:google-drive"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Search and access files from Google Drive. Use when: the user asks to search their Google Drive, find documents, locate files by name, browse their Drive content, or retrieve file metadata. This skill enables agents to search through the user's Google Drive and discover files without needing direct API credentials."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:gpt-research"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"FAST research for quick overviews and initial exploration. Use when you need: (1) Quick research in ~2 minutes with 10-20 sources, (2) Rapid iteration and brainstorming, (3) Internal briefings where speed matters more than comprehensive coverage, (4) Initial exploration before deciding if deep research is needed, (5) Cost-efficient research at ~$0.01/query. NOT for academic research, publication-quality work, or when you need 40+ authoritative sources - use deep-research skill instead for those cases."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:kimi-cli-help"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Answer Kimi Code CLI usage, configuration, and troubleshooting questions. Use when user asks about Kimi Code CLI installation, setup, configuration, slash commands, keyboard shortcuts, MCP integration, providers, environment variables, how something works internally, or any questions about Kimi Code CLI itself."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:kimi-planning"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Activate plan-first workflow mode for Kimi Code CLI to analyze before executing. IMPORTANT: DO NOT use if the enhanced-plan-mode extension is active (check for [ENHANCED-PLAN-MODE-EXTENSION-ACTIVE] in context). Use this skill whenever the user mentions planning, creating a plan, wants to think before acting, or asks for /plan mode - BUT ONLY if the extension signal is NOT present. Use for: multi-file changes (3+ files), refactoring tasks, unfamiliar codebases, high-risk operations (auth, payment, infrastructure), architectural decisions, or when user wants approval gates before changes. Also use when user says 'analyze first', 'plan before', 'review changes before', 'let's think this through', 'I want to see the plan', or similar planning-oriented requests. Provides structured Plan → Approve → Execute workflow similar to Claude Code /plan or Aider architect mode."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:markdown-to-docx"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Convert markdown files to Microsoft Word documents (.docx) while preserving headers, bullet points, paragraphs, bold/italic formatting, numbered lists, and basic tables. Use when - (1) User asks to \"convert markdown to Word\", \"export .md as docx\", or \"create Word document from markdown\", (2) Sharing markdown content in Microsoft Word format with others, (3) Creating professionally formatted Word documents from markdown source files, (4) Converting README files, reports, or documentation to .docx format, (5) Producing editable Word documents from markdown for business or academic use. ALWAYS use when user needs a .docx file created from any markdown content. Related - markdown conversion, md to docx, markdown to Word, export markdown, convert .md to .docx, create Word document, markdown export, document conversion, Word file generation, Microsoft Word from markdown, markdown compiler, docx generator."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:mobile-testing"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Iterative mobile-friendly testing workflow combining Google PageSpeed Insights API (scoring + actionable fixes) with Playwright (visual verification). Use when testing website mobile-friendliness, optimizing for mobile performance, fixing mobile usability issues, or validating mobile fixes before/after changes. Provides step-by-step iterative improvement workflow with specific fix recommendations and visual regression testing."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:my-work-email-tone"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Write emails in Valtteri Melkko's warm, mentoring style using BRITISH ENGLISH spelling (colour, honour, centre, organisation). ALWAYS ask if writing to STAFF (@uwe.ac.uk) or STUDENTS (@live.uwe.ac.uk) - these have distinct styles. Staff: collaborative, softening modals, relationship-first. Students: mentoring-supportive, encouraging, options-based guidance. Use when user wants help with work emails in Valtteri's voice."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:n8n-code-javascript"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Write JavaScript code in n8n Code nodes. Use when writing JavaScript in n8n, using $input/$json/$node syntax, making HTTP requests with $helpers, working with dates using DateTime, troubleshooting Code node errors, or choosing between Code node modes."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["path",{"d":"M11 13h4"}],["rect",{"width":"18","height":"18","x":"3","y":"3","rx":"2","ry":"2"}]],["SPAN",{"class":"truncate"},["SPAN",{"class":"font-medium text-primary"},"/","skill:n8n-code-python"],["SPAN",{"class":"ml-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground"},"Write Python code in n8n Code nodes. Use when writing Python in n8n, using _input/_json/_node syntax, working with standard library, or need to understand Python limitations in n8n Code nodes."]]],["BUTTON",{"type":"button","class":"flex w-full items-center gap-2 rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-left text-sm transition-colors my-0.5 hover:bg-muted"},["svg",{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":"24","height":"24","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","stroke-width":"2","stroke-linecap":"round","stroke-linejoin":"round","class":"lucide lucide-square-terminal size-3.5 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground","aria-hidden":"true"},["path",{"d":"m7 11 2-2-2-2"}],["